This paper is primarily focused on the deployment of public Wi-Fi networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also uses a bargaining framework to model the cooperation between the mobile network operator (MNO) and the venue owners (VOs), which involves negotiating payments and deployment locations. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper considers the negative externalities among different steps of bargaining, which could be related to social networks (cs.SI) or computational economics (cs.CE).
